    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect hash computation in trace_hashtable due to pointer size bug\n\n### Summary\nThe hash function in trace_hashtable.c was computing incorrect hash values because it used sizeof(pointer) instead of sizeof(data) when processing the input key. This caused the hash to process memory beyond the actual integer key, leading to unpredictable hash values and potential hashtable lookup failures.\n\nThis fix corrects the hash computation to properly handle integer keys.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/trace_hashtable.c`: Fixed hash function to use sizeof(int) instead of sizeof(key)\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/trace_hashtable.h`: Updated function signature and documentation\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain conditions with specific GID values, nodes were not being found in the hashtable even after insertion. Debugging showed the hash function was returning different values during insertion vs lookup for the same key, due to the incorrect loop bound processing extra memory bytes.\n"
}